* Iron Raptor simply looks over the field one more time before looking at 
Iris as Prowl sets her down, expecting an answer for her question.*

IRIS: " If it's pain that's keeping the aggression of those beast modes 
under controle then no. Injuries shouldn't matter here, besides, both of you 
will come out repaired in the end."

* Iron Raptor growled and looked at Prowl for a moment, then looking back 
towards the field.
But at the mention at her injuries she was, once again, reminded of her 
wounded shoulder, shifting her weight to keep off of it.
Iron Raptor turned her head in surprise towards Prowl as he layed a 
concerned hand on her shoulder, seeing his equally sight of concern as well

She sighed and leaned against him a bit, but not too much because she might 
push him over.
She was tired, sore, in pain and just sick of everything. She just wanted 
this over and done with so that she could get back to the CF and being 
commander of the Maximals.*

IRIS: " Prowl, if you're ready maybe we could start?"
